ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-dns_cache_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

The length of time, in milliseconds, the program should continue to refer to the previously resolved host name stored in its cache before discarding the entry and accessing the DNS server to re-resolve the host name.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify; -target client

DEFAULT

 None

-dns_enable

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Enables the use of DNS on the associated network.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify; -target client

DEFAULT

 None

-dns_server

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Defines DNS servers to be used for lookups. When -mode add a list of servers can be provided. DNS is only supported with IPv4.Dependencies: -property must be dns; -mode add | modify; target client

DEFAULT

 None

-dns_suffix

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Define suffixes to be appended to partial host names. Each is tried in order by the DNS server(s). When -mode add a list of suffixes can be provided.

DEFAULT

 None

-emulated_router_gateway

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If mac_mapping_mode is set to macport, then an emulated router is inserted between the clients and the external port. This is the gateway to be used for that router.Dependencies: mac_mapping_mode macport; -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

0.0.0.0

-emulated_router_subnet

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If mac_mapping_mode is set to macport, then an emulated router is inserted between the clients and the external port. This is the network mask to be used for that router. For ipv6 network masks a prefix length value will be used (e.g. -emulated_router_subnet 96)Dependencies: mac_mapping_mode macport; -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

255.255.255.0)

-grat_arp_enable

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If true, before beginning a test, IxLoad ARPs the gateways so that the DUT can learn the MAC addresses used on the subnet. If a subnet is set to MAC per Port, the subnet sends one ARP request. If a subnet is set to MAC per IP, each host on the subnet sends an ARP request.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

0

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Dependencies: property network | network_pool | router_pool | dnsnetwork_handle - used when -property is network and -mode is remove | modifynetwork_handle - used when -property is network_pool | router_pool | dns and -mode is addnetwork_pool_handle - used when -property is network_pool and -mode is modify | remove | enable | disable.router_pool_handle - used when -property is router_pool and -mode is modify | remove | enable | disabledns_server_handle - used when -property is dns and -mode is modify | remove and target clientdns_suffix_handle - used when -property is dns and -mode is modify | remove and target client

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_mapping_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Indicates whether one MAC address will be associated with each IP address or with each port. The use of the latter option indicates that an emulated router is to be used.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

macip

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad [M]

DESCRIPTION

Defines types of actions to be taken on the -property object.

DEFAULT

 None

-ip_type

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Type of IP address. This parameter indicates whether the address range is a range of IPv4 addresses or a range of IPv6 addresses. Only HTTP and FTP agents support IPv6.If the ip_type parameter is not provided it will be auto detected using the np_first_ip(for -property network_pool) or rp_first_ip (for -property router_pool).Dependencies: -property must be network_pool or router_pool; mode add | modify

DEFAULT

 None

-np_ac_name

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Specifies the name of access concentrator. (Default = "ac name").Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type pppoe; np_ac_selection match_name

DEFAULT

 None

-np_ac_selection

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

(DEFAULT =CHOICES match_first) This option helps to choose an access concentrator, and it can be either kMatch-First, kMatchName or kMatchService. MatchFirst indicates the first server to response, MatchName indicates the specified access concentrator name and MatchService indicates the service.Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type pppoe

DEFAULT

 None

-np_auth_retries

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If the initial authentication attempt fails, this option specifies how many additional authentication attempts the client will make.Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type pppoe

DEFAULT

 None

-np_auth_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Length of time allowed for the access concentrator to authenticate the client. If this time elapses with no response, the client reattempts authentication until the number of attempts equals the value in the authRetries option. Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type pppoe

DEFAULT

 None

-np_auth_type

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Valid options are:

none

No authentication

pap

PAP authentication will be used. Configure the PAP User Name

chap

CHAP authentication will be used.

pap_or_chap

Either PAP or CHAP will be used, at the request of

DEFAULT

 None

-np_first_ip

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

The first IP address for the range. If ipType is set to "IPv4" this must be an IPv4 address. If ipType is set to "IPv6," this must be an IPv6 address. Only HTTP and FTP agents support IPv6 addressing. If there is a mixture of IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, other protocols will use only the IPv4 addresses. IxLoad supports all forms of IPv6 addressing except ::dotted-quad notation (for example, "::1.2.3.4").Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type ethernet

DEFAULT

198.18.0.1)

DEFAULT

 None

-np_inner_vlan_count

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Indicates the number of vLAN IDs that will be used on traffic from the network. IxLoad divides the number of hosts on the network by the number of vLAN IDs, and distributes the hosts evenly across all the vLAN IDs. Any remaining hosts are added to the final vLAN ID.Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type ethernet

DEFAULT

 None

-np_inner_vlan_enable

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If checked, IxLoad encapsulates the vLAN-tagged frame inside another frame with a second vLAN tag.Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type ethernet

DEFAULT

 None

-tcp_enable_congestion_notification

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If true, the client or server uses bits from the Type of Service (TOS) field and the TCP packet header's Reserved field to support Explicit Congestion Notification (ECN). ECN uses the bits as follows:TOS bit 6 is the ECT (Explicit Congestion Transport) bit, which a recipient sets to indicate that it supports ECN.TOS bit 7 is the CE (Congestion Experienced) bit, which the recipient sets if its average queue length exceeds a threshold.TCP header Reserved field bit 5 the CWR (Congestion Window Reduced) bit.TCP header Reserved field bit 6 is the ECN-Echo bit.A SYN packet with both ECN-Echo and CWR bits indicates the sender supports ECN in both directions (as sender and receiver). A combined SYN+ACK packet sets only ECN to indicate ECN capability.If you enable ECN, the sender sets the ECT bit to indicate that it supports ECN. If the sender receives a packet with the CE bit set, it returns an ACK with the ECN-Echo bit set. If a sender receives a packet with ECN-Echo set, it should reduce its window size. The first packet it sends after reducing its window size has the CWR bit set. The sender will repeatedly reduce its window size until it receives a packet in return with the CWR bit from the recipient.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

 None

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

dns_cache_timeout

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

The length of time, in milliseconds, the program should continue to refer to the previously resolved host name stored in its cache before discarding the entry and accessing the DNS server to re-resolve the host name.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify; -target client

DEFAULT

 None

dns_enable

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Enables the use of DNS on the associated network.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify; -target client

DEFAULT

 None

dns_server

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Defines DNS servers to be used for lookups. When -mode add a list of servers can be provided. DNS is only supported with IPv4.Dependencies: -property must be dns; -mode add | modify; target client

DEFAULT

 None

dns_suffix

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Define suffixes to be appended to partial host names. Each is tried in order by the DNS server(s). When -mode add a list of suffixes can be provided.

DEFAULT

 None

emulated_router_gateway

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If mac_mapping_mode is set to macport, then an emulated router is inserted between the clients and the external port. This is the gateway to be used for that router.Dependencies: mac_mapping_mode macport; -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

0.0.0.0

emulated_router_subnet

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If mac_mapping_mode is set to macport, then an emulated router is inserted between the clients and the external port. This is the network mask to be used for that router. For ipv6 network masks a prefix length value will be used (e.g. -emulated_router_subnet 96)Dependencies: mac_mapping_mode macport; -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

255.255.255.0)

grat_arp_enable

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If true, before beginning a test, IxLoad ARPs the gateways so that the DUT can learn the MAC addresses used on the subnet. If a subnet is set to MAC per Port, the subnet sends one ARP request. If a subnet is set to MAC per IP, each host on the subnet sends an ARP request.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

0

handle

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Dependencies: property network | network_pool | router_pool | dnsnetwork_handle - used when -property is network and -mode is remove | modifynetwork_handle - used when -property is network_pool | router_pool | dns and -mode is addnetwork_pool_handle - used when -property is network_pool and -mode is modify | remove | enable | disable.router_pool_handle - used when -property is router_pool and -mode is modify | remove | enable | disabledns_server_handle - used when -property is dns and -mode is modify | remove and target clientdns_suffix_handle - used when -property is dns and -mode is modify | remove and target client

DEFAULT

 None

DEFAULT

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Type of IP address. This parameter indicates whether the address range is a range of IPv4 addresses or a range of IPv6 addresses. Only HTTP and FTP agents support IPv6.If the ip_type parameter is not provided it will be auto detected using the np_first_ip(for -property network_pool) or rp_first_ip (for -property router_pool).Dependencies: -property must be network_pool or router_pool; mode add | modify

DEFAULT

 None

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

Length of time allowed for the access concentrator to authenticate the client. DEFAULT

np_first_ip

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

The first IP address for the range. If ipType is set to "IPv4" this must be an IPv4 address. If ipType is set to "IPv6," this must be an IPv6 address. Only HTTP and FTP agents support IPv6 addressing. If there is a mixture of IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, other protocols will use only the IPv4 addresses. IxLoad supports all forms of IPv6 addressing except ::dotted-quad notation (for example, "::1.2.3.4").Dependencies: -property must be network_pool; -mode add | modify; np_range_type ethernet

DEFAULT

198.18.0.1)

tcp_enable_congestion_notification

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If true, the client or server uses bits from the Type of Service (TOS) field and the TCP packet header's Reserved field to support Explicit Congestion Notification (ECN). ECN uses the bits as follows:TOS bit 6 is the ECT (Explicit Congestion Transport) bit, which a recipient sets to indicate that it supports ECN.TOS bit 7 is the CE (Congestion Experienced) bit, which the recipient sets if its average queue length exceeds a threshold.TCP header Reserved field bit 5 the CWR (Congestion Window Reduced) bit.TCP header Reserved field bit 6 is the ECN-Echo bit.A SYN packet with both ECN-Echo and CWR bits indicates the sender supports ECN in both directions (as sender and receiver). A combined SYN+ACK packet sets only ECN to indicate ECN capability.If you enable ECN, the sender sets the ECT bit to indicate that it supports ECN. If the sender receives a packet with the CE bit set, it returns an ACK with the ECN-Echo bit set. If a sender receives a packet with ECN-Echo set, it should reduce its window size. The first packet it sends after reducing its window size has the CWR bit set. The sender will repeatedly reduce its window size until it receives a packet in return with the CWR bit from the recipient.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

 None

tcp_enable_congestion_notification

Supported platforms Details

IxLoad

DESCRIPTION

If true, the client or server uses bits from the Type of Service (TOS) field and the TCP packet header's Reserved field to support Explicit Congestion Notification (ECN). ECN uses the bits as follows:TOS bit 6 is the ECT (Explicit Congestion Transport) bit, which a recipient sets to indicate that it supports ECN.TOS bit 7 is the CE (Congestion Experienced) bit, which the recipient sets if its average queue length exceeds a threshold.TCP header Reserved field bit 5 the CWR (Congestion Window Reduced) bit.TCP header Reserved field bit 6 is the ECN-Echo bit.A SYN packet with both ECN-Echo and CWR bits indicates the sender supports ECN in both directions (as sender and receiver). A combined SYN+ACK packet sets only ECN to indicate ECN capability.If you enable ECN, the sender sets the ECT bit to indicate that it supports ECN. If the sender receives a packet with the CE bit set, it returns an ACK with the ECN-Echo bit set. If a sender receives a packet with ECN-Echo set, it should reduce its window size. The first packet it sends after reducing its window size has the CWR bit set. The sender will repeatedly reduce its window size until it receives a packet in return with the CWR bit from the recipient.Dependencies: -property network; -mode add | modify

DEFAULT

 None
